muslimtify (0.2.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Replace the per-minute systemd timer with a long-running, self-scheduling daemon ("daemon run")
  * Ship the systemd user unit as a long-running Type=simple service with Restart=on-failure; remove muslimtify.timer entirely
  * Sleep in bounded, interruptible naps aligned to the top of each minute, so a suspend/resume or clock change cannot overshoot or skip a prayer
  * Handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown instead of being killed mid-sleep
  * Disable and remove a leftover muslimtify.timer on install and uninstall; postinst calls "daemon install", so PPA upgrades self-heal with no manual steps
  * Keep "muslimtify check" working unchanged for manual runs or custom scheduling
  * Add unit tests for the systemd unit builder and the loop sleep interval

